  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "From the [`abstract` documentation](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/contracts.html#abstract-contracts), it seems like what the keyword does is mark the contract as non-deployable (i.e. it needs to be inherited from). Because contracts missing function implementations are always non-deployable, they require `abstract`.\r\n\r\nIf this is the case, shouldn't `abstract` be required also for contracts with `constructor() internal`?",
